'''Ram<U+00F3>n A. Ram<U+00ED>rez''' (born September 16, 1982 in [[Cagua]], [[Venezuela]]) is a [[Venezuela]]n [[pitcher]] who is currently a [[free agent]]. He stands {{convert|6|ft|m}} tall and weighs {{convert|190|lb|kg}}. Previously, he has pitched for the [[Cincinnati Reds]]. He bats and throws right-handed. He throws three pitches: a [[fastball]], a [[slider]], and a [[changeup]].

Ram<U+00ED>rez was signed by the [[San Diego Padres]] in 2000 as an [[outfielder]], but he was released in 2001. The Reds signed him in 2003 as a pitcher, and he reached the major leagues in 2008, when he made four starts for the Reds. The next year, he appeared in 11 games in relief for the Reds. After the season, the [[Tampa Bay Rays]] claimed him off waivers, but they released him. The [[Boston Red Sox]] claimed him off waivers, and he spent 2010 in the minor leagues for them. He signed with the [[Doosan Bears]] of the [[Korean Baseball Organization]] in 2011, but he was released before appearing in a game with them.

==Professional career==
===San Diego Padres===
On March 27, 2000, Ram<U+00ED>rez was signed by the [[San Diego Padres]] as an [[outfielder]].<ref name="MLB">{{cite web |url=http://mlb.mlb.com/team/player.jsp?player_id=459371 |title=Ramon A. Ramirez Stats, Bio, Photos, Highlights |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com]] |accessdate=2011-11-01}}</ref><ref name="reference">{{cite web |url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/players/r/ramirra03.shtml |title=Ramon Ramirez Statistics and History |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] |accessdate=2011-11-01}}</ref> He was released by the Padres on June 12, 2001.<ref name="reference"/>

===Cincinnati Reds===
====2004-2007====
On May 12, 2003, Ram<U+00ED>rez was signed by the [[Cincinnati Reds]], this time as a [[pitcher]].<ref name="reference"/><ref name="MLB"/> In 2004, he pitched for the [[Billings Mustangs]] of the [[Pioneer League (baseball)|Pioneer League]], a rookie league.<ref name="minors">{{cite web |url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/player.cgi?id=ramire002ram |title=Ramon Ramirez Minor League Statistics & History |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] (Minors) |accessdate=2011-11-02}}</ref> In 17 [[Games played|games]] (12 [[Games started|starts]]), he had three wins and six losses, which was tied for fourth in the league.<ref name="minors"/><ref name="Pioneer League Leaders">{{cite web |url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/leader.cgi?type=pitch&id=d9aa4119 |title=2004 Pioneer League Pitching Leaders |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] (Minors) |accessdate=2011-11-03}}</ref> However, he was 10th in the league in [[strikeouts]] (60), third in [[innings pitched]] ({{frac|74|1|3}}), and second in [[earned run average]] (3.39, behind only [[Samuel Deduno]]'s 3.18 ERA).<ref name="Pioneer League Leaders"/>

In 2005, Ram<U+00ED>rez pitched for the [[Dayton Dragons]] of the [[single-A]] [[Midwest League]].<ref name="minors"/> He had a 5<U+2013>7 [[Win-loss record (pitching)|record]], a 4.50 ERA, 114 innings pitched, and 90 strikeouts in 30 games (19 starts).<ref name="minors"/>

Ram<U+00ED>rez pitched for the [[Sarasota Reds]] of the [[single-A advanced]] [[Florida State League]] in 2006.<ref name="minors"/> He had a 4<U+2013>5 record, a 4.29 ERA, 53 strikeouts, 65 innings pitched, and one [[complete game]] in 15 games (11 starts).<ref name="minors"/>

In 2007, Ram<U+00ED>rez began the year with Sarasota again.<ref name="MLB"/> He had a 5<U+2013>2 record, a 4.05 ERA, {{frac|73|1|3}} innings pitched, and 86 strikeouts in 15 games (12 starts); and he was promoted to the [[Chattanooga Lookouts]] of the [[double-A]] [[Southern League (baseball)|Southern League]] on June 22.<ref name="MLB"/><ref name="minors"/> At Chattanooga, used exclusively as a [[relief pitcher]], he had a 5<U+2013>1 record, a 4.60 ERA, {{frac|31|1|3}} innings pitched, and 35 strikeouts in 16 games.<ref name="minors"/> On August 18, he was promoted to the [[Louisville Bats]] of the [[Triple-A (baseball)|triple-A]] [[International League]] to replace [[Elizardo Ram<U+00ED>rez]], who was called up to the Reds.<ref name="MLB"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20070817&content_id=2154423&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Notes: Ramirez to start on Saturday |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2007-08-17 |accessdate=2011-11-17}}</ref> With Louisville, Ram<U+00F3>n Ram<U+00ED>rez had a 1<U+2013>0 record, an 0.00 ERA, {{frac|14|2|3}} innings pitched, and 16 strikeouts in five games (two starts).<ref name="minors"/> In the minor leagues that year, he had 11 wins (tied for fourth in the Reds' system), 3 losses, a 3.70 ERA (ninth), {{frac|119|1|3}} innings pitched, and 137 strikeouts (second) in 36 games (14 starts).<ref name="MLB"/><ref name="minors"/> The Cincinnati Reds added him to their [[40-man roster]] on November 20.<ref name="MLB"/>

====2008====
Ram<U+00ED>rez attended [[2008 Cincinnati Reds season|Reds']] [[spring training]] in {{mlby|2008}} but was optioned to the minors on March 10 after having an 11.57 ERA in three games.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080310&content_id=2417115&vkey=spt2008news&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds cut two pitchers from spring camp |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-03-10 |accessdate=2012-01-09}}</ref> He began the season with Chattanooga.<ref name="MLB"/> After he had a 2<U+2013>3 record, a 4.70 ERA, 46 innings pitched, and 52 strikeouts in 11 games (nine starts), he was promoted to Louisville on May 23.<ref name="minors"/><ref name="MLB"/> At Louisville, he had a 4<U+2013>5 record, a 3.08 ERA, {{frac|99|1|3}} innings pitched, and 93 strikeouts in 19 games (15 starts).<ref name="minors"/> On August 30, he was called up to the Reds make a start that day in place of the injured [[Johnny Cueto]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Wallner |first=Jeff |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080830&content_id=3391534&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds bring in Ramirez, option Rosales |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-08-30 |accessdate=2011-12-13}}</ref> He gave up three runs over seven innings while striking out six, but he received a [[no decision]] in a 7<U+2013>6 victory over the [[2008 San Francisco Giants season|San Francisco Giants]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Wallner |first=Jeff |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080830&content_id=3391368&vkey=recap&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Patterson leads late rally over Giants |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-08-31 |accessdate=2011-12-14}}</ref> He was optioned to Sarasota the next day to make room for [[Wilkin Castillo]] on the roster but was recalled on September 2.<ref>{{cite web |last=Wallner |first=Jeff |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080831&content_id=3395829&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds exchange one debut for another |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-08-31 |accessdate=2011-12-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080902&content_id=3407439&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Ramirez, Burton rejoin Reds |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-09-02 |accessdate=2011-12-15}}</ref> On September 4, he threw three perfect innings in relief of an injured [[Josh Fogg]] in an 8<U+2013>6 victory over the [[2008 Pittsburgh Pirates season|Pittsburgh Pirates]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080904&content_id=3418121&vkey=recap&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds rally to upend Bucs in finale |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-09-04 |accessdate=2011-12-27}}</ref> Afterwards, he made three more starts for the Reds.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/tgl.cgi?team=CIN&t=p&year=2008 |title=2008 Cincinnati Reds Pitching Gamelogs |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] |accessdate=2011-12-30}}</ref> He got his first career decision (a win) on September 19 when he gave up two runs and struck out five batters in six innings as the Reds defeated the [[2008 Milwaukee Brewers season|Milwaukee Brewers]], 11<U+2013>2.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080919&content_id=3510081&vkey=recap&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Powering up: Reds cruise past Crew |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-09-19 |accessdate=2011-12-30}}</ref> He got his only other decision of the year on September 24, when he gave up two runs in five innings in a 5<U+2013>0 loss to the [[2008 Houston Astros season|Houston Astros]].<ref name="starting spot">{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080924&content_id=3542800&vkey=recap&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds unable to back Ramirez |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2008-09-25 |accessdate=2012-01-10}}</ref> Ram<U+00ED>rez finished the [[2008 Cincinnati Reds season|year]] 1<U+2013>1, with a 2.67 ERA, 21 strikeouts, and 27 innings pitched in 5 games (4 starts).<ref name="MLB"/> In the minors, he had a 6<U+2013>8 record, a 3.59 ERA, 145 strikeouts, and {{frac|145|1|3}} innings pitched in 30 games (24 starts).<ref name="minors"/>

====2009====
Ram<U+00ED>rez was expected to compete for a spot in the [[2009 Cincinnati Reds season|Reds']] starting rotation in {{mlby|2009}}; however, because he missed much of spring training at the [[2009 World Baseball Classic|World Baseball Classic]], he began the year with Louisville.<ref>{{cite web |last=Mayo |first=Jonathan |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090323&content_id=4055132&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Six more cut from Reds roster |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2009-03-23 |accessdate=2012-01-16}}</ref> On May 19, he was called up from Louisville to replace the injured [[Nick Masset]] in the bullpen.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090519&content_id=4817366&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds like righty Ramirez's versatility |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2009-05-19 |accessdate=2012-01-17}}</ref> After appearing in one game, he was optioned back to Louisville on May 22 to make room for [[Carlos Fisher]] on the roster.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090522&content_id=4882946&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds add veteran Gomes, reliever Fisher |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2009-05-22 |accessdate=2011-01-17}}</ref> He remained in Louisville until August 31, when he was recalled between games of a [[Doubleheader (baseball)|doubleheader]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090831&content_id=6718388&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Reds make three moves before nightcap |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2009-08-31 |accessdate=2011-01-17}}</ref> After giving up 4 runs in his first 3 games of the season, Ram<U+00ED>rez gave up 1 run in his last 8 games.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/players/gl.cgi?id=ramirra03&t=p&year=2009 |title=Ramon Ramirez 2009 Pitching Gamelogs |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=[[Baseball-Reference.com]] |accessdate=2012-01-17}}</ref> Used exclusively out of the bullpen, he finished the [[2009 Cincinnati Reds season|year]] with an 0<U+2013>0 record, a 3.65 ERA, eight strikeouts, and {{frac|12|1|3}} innings pitched in 11 games.<ref name="MLB"/> At Louisville, he had a 6<U+2013>7 record, a 4.03 ERA, 78 strikeouts, and {{frac|127|1|3}} innings pitched in 31 games (20 starts).<ref name="minors"/>

===Tampa Bay Rays/Boston Red Sox===
On November 9, the [[Tampa Bay Rays]] claimed Ram<U+00ED>rez off [[Major League Baseball transactions#Waivers|waivers]],<ref name="Rays waivers">{{cite web |last=Chastain |first=Bill |url=http://tampabay.rays.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20091109&content_id=7642970&vkey=news_tb&fext=.jsp&c_id=tb |title=Crawford's $10M club option exercised |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Rays.MLB.com]] |date=2009-11-09 |accessdate=2012-01-19}}</ref> but they released him on December 3.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chastain |first=Bill |url=http://tampabay.rays.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20091203&content_id=7749356&vkey=news_tb&fext=.jsp&c_id=tb |title=Rays release right-hander Ramirez |work=[[MLB.com|Rays.MLB.com]] |publisher=Major League Baseball |date=2009-12-03 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref> On December 9, the [[Boston Red Sox]] claimed him off waivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tsn.ca/mlb/story/?id=301690 |title=Red Sox sign another Ramon Ramirez |work=[[The Sports Network|TSN]] |date=2009-12-09 |accessdate=2010-08-21}}</ref> He spent the 2010 season with the [[Pawtucket Red Sox]] of the International League, where he had a 5<U+2013>5 record, a 4.92 ERA, one complete game, 97 innings pitched, and 80 strikeouts in 28 games (13 starts).<ref name="minors"/> On November 6, he became a [[free agent]].<ref name="reference"/>

===Doosan Bears===
In 2011, Ram<U+00ED>rez signed with the [[Doosan Bears]] of the [[Korean Baseball Organization]]. However, he was released before playing a regular season game after he struggled in the preseason.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/culturesports/2011/04/06/0702000000AEN20110406000800315.HTML |title=Doosan Bears to release Venezuelan pitcher |work=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=2011-04-06 |accessdate=2011-06-24}}</ref>

==International play==
In 2009, Ram<U+00ED>rez represented [[Venezuela]] in the [[2009 World Baseball Classic|World Baseball Classic]], deciding to play in the tournament at the last minute.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sheldon |first=Mark |url=http://cincinnati.reds.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090302&content_id=3906032&vkey=news_cin&fext=.jsp&c_id=cin |title=Ramirez departs last-minute for Classic |publisher=Major League Baseball |work=[[MLB.com|Reds.MLB.com]] |date=2009-03-02 |accessdate=2011-01-11}}</ref> On March 10, he gave up one run in three innings of relief as Venezuela defeated [[Italy]] 10<U+2013>1 to advance to the second round of the Classic.<ref>{{cite web |last=Singh |first=David |url=http://web.worldbaseballclassic.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090310&content_id=3960238&vkey=wbc_recap&team=ven |title=Venezuela rides over Italy to next round |publisher=World Baseball Classic |work=worldbaseballclassic.com |date=2009-03-11 |accessdate=2011-01-11}}</ref>  He pitched a scoreless {{frac|2|3}} of an inning on March 16 as Venezuela defeated [[Puerto Rico]] 2<U+2013>0.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mlb.mlb.com/wbc/2009/stats/boxscore.jsp?gid=2009_03_16_venint_purint_1 |title=Venezuela 2, Puerto Rico 0 |publisher=World Baseball Classic |work=worldbaseballclassic.com |accessdate=2012-01-12}}</ref> In his final game of the Classic (on March 18), Ram<U+00ED>rez gave up two runs in {{frac|1|2|3}} innings, but Venezuela defeated the [[United States]] 10<U+2013>6 to advance to the semifinals.<ref>{{cite web |last=Leach |first=Matthew |url=http://web.worldbaseballclassic.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090318&content_id=4025106&vkey=wbc_recap&team=ven |title=Venezuela leaves Miami as top dog |publisher=World Baseball Classic |work=worldbaseballclassic.com |date=2009-03-19 |accessdate=2011-01-12}}</ref>

==Pitching style==
Ram<U+00ED>rez throws three pitches: a [[fastball]], a [[slider]], and a [[changeup]]. Rays' [[general manager]] [[Andrew Friedman]] described the fastball as "average," the slider as "pretty good," and the changeup as "above-average."<ref name="Rays waivers"/>

